🏡 THE 15-MINUTE FIRST-TIME BUYER STRATEGY CALL

(Under $500K – Port St. Lucie)

⸻

⏱ Minute 0–2: Authority + Frame Control

“Hi [Name], I’m glad we connected.

The goal of this call is simple — by the end of 15 minutes, you’ll know whether buying under $500K in Port St. Lucie makes sense for you right now, later this year, or not yet.

Fair?”

(Wait for agreement.)

This establishes:
• Structure
• Leadership
• Safety

⸻

⏱ Minute 2–5: Timeline & Motivation

“Let me ask — what prompted you to download the blueprint?”

(They talk. You listen.)

Then:

“If everything lined up perfectly, when would you ideally want to be in your own place?”

Key buckets:
• 0–3 months → Hot
• 3–6 months → Warm
• 6–12 months → Nurture

Follow with:

“What would buying change for you?”

This question reveals emotional motivation:
• Stability
• Financial growth
• Family space
• Relocation pressure

Emotion drives action.

⸻

⏱ Minute 5–8: Financial Clarity (Without Pressure)

“Have you spoken with a lender yet?”

If yes:
“What price range did they give you?”

If no:
“Totally fine — most buyers start there. Would it help if we mapped out what under $500K realistically looks like based on your comfort level?”

Important language:
Comfort > Approval

Then:

“What monthly payment would feel safe for you?”

This avoids over-buying and builds trust.

⸻

⏱ Minute 8–11: Neighborhood Alignment

“Are you leaning more toward new construction or resale?”

Then:

“Do you prefer HOA amenities, or flexibility with no HOA?”

Then:

“Have you visited Tradition, St. Lucie West, Becker, or Torino?”

Now you are:
• Diagnosing fit
• Showing local authority
• Positioning yourself as area specialist

You’re not selling homes.

You’re narrowing focus.

⸻

⏱ Minute 11–13: Strategic Insight Drop

This is where you demonstrate expertise.

Example:

“Under $500K in PSL, the homes that move fastest are typically updated 3–4 bedroom properties in growth corridors. Buyers who are pre-approved and clear on neighborhoods tend to secure better terms.”

Pause.

Then:

“The buyers who feel overwhelmed usually haven’t clarified steps yet.”

You are calmly positioning yourself as the solution.

⸻

⏱ Minute 13–15: The Close (Low Pressure)

Now you transition.

Depending on readiness:

⸻

🔥 If They’re Hot (0–3 Months)

“Based on what you’ve shared, the next logical step would be:

1️⃣ Get pre-approved
2️⃣ Narrow to 2 target neighborhoods
3️⃣ Schedule strategic showings

Would you like me to connect you with a lender and start mapping this out?”

Stop talking.

Let them answer.

⸻

🌤 If They’re Warm (3–6 Months)

“You’re in a great position to plan early.

Let’s get your financing clarity first so when the right home appears, you’re ready — not reactive.

Does that feel like a good next step?”

⸻

🌱 If They’re Nurture (6–12 Months)

“Perfect. You don’t need to rush.

Let’s set you up with:
• Monthly under-$500K updates
• Financing overview
• Neighborhood comparison guide

And when you’re ready, we activate.”

⸻

💬 Objection Handling

If they say:
“We’re just looking.”

Reply:

“Totally fair. Most buyers say that before they realize they’re closer than they think. My job isn’t to rush you — it’s to help you make a smart decision when the timing is right.”

If they say:
“We’re worried about rates.”

Reply:

“Rates matter. But strategy matters more. Builders are offering incentives, sellers are negotiating in certain segments, and waiting doesn’t always improve leverage. The key is evaluating your specific scenario.”

Calm. Never defensive.

⸻

🎯 The Final Line (Every Call)

“Whether you move forward now or later, I want you to feel clear and confident. That’s the goal.”

This makes you the guide, not the salesperson.

⸻

📈 After The Call

Immediately:

• Send summary email
• Send lender intro if needed
• Send 3 sample listings in their target range
• Set follow-up date

Momentum wins.

